# =============================================================================
# =============================================================================
#                    PRODUCTION EVENT CATEGORIZATION WEBAPP
# =============================================================================
# =============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
#   Web application for categorizing production DOWNTIME and SLOWTIME events.
#   Operators use this to assign reason codes to events and track production.
#
# MAIN FEATURES:
#   1. Event Categorization View (default)
#      - Lists all DOWNTIME/SLOWTIME events for selected shift
#      - User assigns category codes (A1-I1) with durations
#      - Multiple categories per event supported (e.g., 30min A1 + 20min B2)
#      - User can add comments per event
#      - Auto-assigns G1 to SLOWTIME events
#
#   2. HRxHR View (Hour by Hour)
#      - Bar chart showing bobbin production per hour
#      - Table showing downtime per hour with color coding
#      - First hour shows actual production (cumulative value for that hour)
#      - Handles event spillover across hours
#
# DATA FLOW:
#   Events_Stacked (source) → Webapp displays events
#   User categorizes events → TRSP_APP_DATA (annotations saved)
#   Bobbin_Counts → Displayed in HRxHR view
#
# SHIFT SYSTEM:
#   - Shift A: 06:00 - 18:00 (day shift)
#   - Shift B: 18:00 - 06:00 (night shift, crosses midnight)
#   - Navigation buttons to move between shifts
#
# CATEGORY CODES (45 total):
#   A = Equipment, B = Material, C = Process, D = Quality,
#   E = Planning, F = Changeover, G = Speed Loss, H = External, I = Other
#
# =============================================================================
# PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATIONS:
# =============================================================================
#   1. DATA CACHING:
#      - 2-minute TTL cache for dataset reads (reduces Dataiku API calls)
#      - Cache auto-invalidates on save operations
#      - Cache key based on time slots for predictable refresh
#
#   2. VECTORIZED PANDAS OPERATIONS:
#      - Annotation merge uses pd.merge() instead of row iteration
#      - G1 auto-assignment uses boolean masks instead of iterrows()
#      - ~100x faster for datasets with 200+ rows
#
#   3. PRE-COMPUTED LOOKUPS:
#      - REASON_COLOR_MAP: O(1) color lookup by code
#      - REASON_LABEL_MAP: O(1) label lookup by code
#      - REASON_DROPDOWN_OPTIONS: Pre-built dropdown options list
#
#   4. DASH BEST PRACTICES:
#      - suppress_callback_exceptions for pattern-matching callbacks
#      - prevent_initial_callbacks to reduce load-time triggers
#      - Session storage (dcc.Store) for client-side state
#      - Efficient callback chaining with minimal server round-trips
#
#   5. DATAIKU BEST PRACTICES:
#      - skip_additional_data_checks=True for faster dataset reads
#      - Vectorized to_dict('index') instead of iterrows() for dict building
#      - Proper error handling with fallbacks
#
# =============================================================================

